description.undefined: The Friend of a Friend (FOAF) RDF vocabulary, described using W3C RDF Schema and the Web Ontology Language.

comment.undefined: An agent (eg. person, group, software or physical artifact).
An online account.
An online gaming account.
An organization.
A person.
An online chat account.
A document.
An image.
A foaf:LabelProperty is any RDF property with texual values that serve as labels.
An online e-commerce account.
A class of Agents.
A project (a collective endeavour of some kind).
A personal profile RDF document.
A tipjar document for this agent, describing means for payment and reward.
A workplace homepage of some person; the homepage of an organization they work for.
An agent that  made this thing.
A location that something is based near, for some broadly human notion of near.
A depiction of some thing.
A logo representing some thing.
A page or document about this thing.
Something that was made by this agent.
The birthday of this Agent, represented in mm-dd string form, eg. '12-31'.
A topic of some page or document.
Indicates an account held by this agent.
A document that this thing is the primary topic of.
The family name of some person.
A homepage for some thing.
A string expressing what the user is happy for the general public (normally) to know about their current activity.
The first name of a person.
Title (Mr, Mrs, Ms, Dr. etc)
A current project this person works on.
An AIM chat ID
A thing of interest to this person.
A checksum for the DNA of some thing. Joke.
A sha1sum hash, in hex.
A thing depicted in this representation.
A weblog of some thing (whether person, group, company etc.).
The gender of this Agent (typically but not necessarily 'male' or 'female').
A name for some thing.
The surname of some person.
Indicates a member of a Group
An MSN chat ID
The family name of some person.
A Skype ID
The given name of some person.
Indicates a homepage of the service provide for this online account.
The primary topic of some page or document.
A theme.
The age in years of some agent.

A  personal mailbox, ie. an Internet mailbox associated with exactly one owner, the first owner of this mailbox. This is a 'static inverse functional property', in that  there is (across time and change) at most one individual that ever has any particular value for foaf:mbox.
The last name of a person.
A work info homepage of some person; a page about their work for some organization.
A Yahoo chat ID
A project this person has previously worked on.
A derived thumbnail image.
A short informal nickname characterising an agent (includes login identifiers, IRC and other chat nicknames).
The underlying or 'focal' entity associated with some SKOS-described concept.
A person known by this person (indicating some level of reciprocated interaction between the parties).
A .plan comment, in the tradition of finger and '.plan' files.
A phone,  specified using fully qualified tel: URI scheme (refs: http://www.w3.org/Addressing/schemes.html#tel).

label.undefined: sha1sum of a personal mailbox URI name

comment.undefined: The sha1sum of the URI of an Internet mailbox associated with exactly one owner, the  first owner of the mailbox.
An organization funding a project or person.
Indicates an account held by this agent.
A textual geekcode for this person, see http://www.geekcode.com/geek.html
A link to the publications of this person.
Indicates the name (identifier) associated with this online account.
An ICQ chat ID
An image that can be used to represent some thing (ie. those depictions which are particularly representative of something, eg. one's photo on a homepage).
A page about a topic of interest to this person.
An OpenID for an Agent.
The given name of some person.
A Myers Briggs (MBTI) personality classification.
A jabber ID for something.
A homepage of a school attended by the person.
